    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think they are already providing this using the `ERC20Metadata` extension as this is an optional information that some tokens may not expose. You can use that interface (`IERC20Metadata`) in your contracts if you are sure the tokens you manage/will manage expose this information.  \r\n\r\nCheck [here](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/extensions/IERC20Metadata.sol) if this works for you.\r\n",
